Title: FT-IR Spectrophotometry and Gas Chromatography in the       Undergraduate Chemistry Curriculum
Abstract: The Department of Technology and Physical Science is purchasing                 a gas chromatograph and a Fourier transform infrared                            spectrophotometer for use in organic chemistry.  Students are                   using the instruments to study reaction mechanisms, establish                   the identity and amounts of the intermediates and products                      obtained from reactions, investigate reaction rates.

Title: Curriculum Improvement in Physiology Laboratory Courses
